description.displayText: Daphne has been caring for my 16 month old ever since she was 11 months old.  I don't know where to begin about how wonderful she is.  I was nervous about hiring a stranger to care for my only child. I interviewed several nannies and I knew Daphne was "the one" right away. I went with my maternal instincts and I am so glad I did. My daughter LOVES Daphne.  Daphne is great with my child-very engaging, playful, loving and careful.  She brought a composition book with her and since day 1 she has been recording my child's everyday activities, nap, feeding and diaper changes.  Daphne keeps me up to date via text regularly during the day.  She is happy to do light house keeping and I always come home to a neat + tidy home.  She is an extremely honest person and is never on her cellphone.   Daphne is more then a nanny to us, she has become a part of the family. My husband and I are both physicians w/hectic schedules and she makes our lives much easier. I recommend Daphne without reservation!

description.displayText: Daphne has been taking care of our 14-month-old son several days a week for the last 3 months. We are moving out of the area, so unfortunately we won't be able to continue with her. Daphne always arrives on time or early and is flexible with our unpredictable work schedules. Our son is very happy with her --she gives him 100% of her attention. I feel completely confident my son is in good hands when I leave him with her. In addition to classes or activities I've set up, Daphne takes him for walks, plays with him at the playground, reads, sings songs and plays games with him in our home. Daphne closely follows any schedule I leave and keeps me updated throughout the day about how he is doing. She is receptive to any feedback and offered to read books I had on napping and toddler development. We will miss her very much!

description.displayText: I interviewed, checked the references and trialed Daphne and was very impressed by her. It was really hard to choose between her and the one we ended up going with so I'd love to endorse her. I set the bar very high, I was looking for someone with a lot of experience, childhood care qualifications, CPR certified, happy to do housework and able to speak fluent Spanish and English. She had all of this and more. I found her to be extremely pleasant, kind, respectful and warm. Her references were also excellent. We wish her all the best in her search and any family would be very lucky to have her!

description.displayText: Daphne is so caring, loving and nurturing. She is a bible teacher for children. She loves to help others. She really cares about children and the youth today. Daphne is honest, reliable, trustworthy, and respectful. I've witnessed her interaction with her own children as well. They love her. She is a good role model to others and knows that she is a living example of Jesus so she strives to do her best. I would recommend her to everyone. I've always admired her integrity. That's my review of Daphne.
